In this article, President Barack Obama issues a proclamation declaring the third Saturday of every May as Armed Forces Day. He calls upon all Americans to learn more about and express gratitude for the efforts of the men and women in the military. President Obama acknowledges the sacrifices made by military families and thanks them for their contributions. He also encourages citizens to display the flag of the United States at their homes on Armed Forces Day and volunteer at organizations that support troops. This proclamation supersedes a previous one issued in 2002.